  {
    "reg_id": "REG-001",
    "clause": "Art6(1)",
    "considered_references": [
      "Art9(2)",
      "Art8(1)"
    ],
    "deviation_found": true,
    "deviations": [
      {
        "deviation_type": "Severity deviation",
        "analysis": "Art6(1)(a) requires the data subject’s consent for processing personal data; it does not require that consent to be explicit for ordinary (non-special-category) data. The policy states \"Insofar as you have explicitly consented, Art 6 para 1 lit a) GDPR is the legal basis for the data transfer,\" which elevates the consent threshold above Art6(1)(a). Explicit consent is the threshold typically associated with special categories under Art9(2)(a) (REG-009). Thus, relative to Art6(1), the policy’s phrasing is stricter than required (over-compliance)."
      }
    ],
