        "analysis": "Art21(2) grants a right to object at any time to processing for direct marketing purposes, which includes profiling related to such marketing. The policy states an objection right specifically to 'this use'—email marketing of similar goods and services using contact details obtained in connection with a sale. This channel- and purpose-limited phrasing potentially narrows the scope of the right compared to Art21(2), which applies to any direct marketing regardless of channel or whether offers are 'similar'."
